<subSubSection id="C307E19DFFF00B6AFF428192B8ABFE6F" pageId="8" pageNumber="182" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA2B216FFF00B6AFF428192B8ABFE6F" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="8" pageNumber="182">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFF00B6AFF428192B97EFF1F" bold="true" box="[199,315,223,249]" pageId="8" pageNumber="182">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1DC995FFF00B6AFEC48192BA66FF1F" authorityName="Fauvel" authorityYear="1867" box="[321,547,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Anthobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andicola">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFF00B6AFEC48192BA66FF1F" box="[321,547,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="182">Anthobium andicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from “Chillan” (Chillán, Ňuble Region in the Diguillin Province of 
<collectingCountry id="F30AF286FFF00B6AFE9A804EB924FEF8" box="[287,353,259,286]" name="Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="182">Chile</collectingCountry>
). Coffait &amp; Saiz (1968) transferred this species to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DC995FFF00B6AFC78804EBDDDFEFB" authority="Coiffait &amp; Saiz, 1968" authorityName="Coiffait &amp; Saiz" authorityYear="1968" box="[1021,1432,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xenanthobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFF00B6AFC78804EBCE5FEFB" box="[1021,1184,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="182">Xenanthobium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFF00B6AFB22804EBDDDFEFB" author="Coiffait, H. &amp; Saiz, F." box="[1191,1432,259,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="182" pagination="339 - 468" refId="ref4921" refString="Coiffait, H. &amp; Saiz, F. (1968) Les Staphylinidae (sensu lato) du Chile. In: Deboutteville, C. &amp; Rapoport, E. (Eds.), Biologie de Amerique Australe. Etudes sur la faune du sol. 4. Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique, Paris, pp. 339 - 468." type="book chapter" year="1968">Coiffait &amp; Saiz, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. New records are located about 
<quantity id="4CE51FF3FFF00B6AFE74806ABA00FEA7" box="[497,581,295,321]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="182" unit="km" value="300.0">300 km</quantity>
to the south from the 
<typeStatus id="54A60CB4FFF00B6AFCBF806ABB2FFEA7" box="[826,874,295,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="182">type</typeStatus>
locality. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="1326AE93FFF00B6AFBEC806ABCE8FEA7" box="[1129,1197,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,189,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-16@4.[152,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Habitus of species of Omaliini: 1—Omaliopsis russata (male, syntype), 2—O. russata (Chile, Aguas Calientes), 3—O. struyvei (holotype), 4—Stenomalium picipennis (syntype), 5—S. sp. (female; Chile, Corral), 6—Xenanthobium andicola (Chile, Corral). Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581688/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="182">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
. Aedeagus as in 
